			<p>Growing up in the sixties and seventies I was very attracted to the counterculture that emerged at that&nbsp;time.</p>

			<p>That was the first time when we could see what our planet looked like from space and the first time that young people around the world felt they were part of a global movement that was more important and more theirs, than their own nations.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="right">
			<p>The movement spawned many visionaries but it was the Whole Earth team under the guidance of Stewart Brand and later Kevin Kelly (still curating his CoolTools site) that really emphasized the importance of “ Access to Tools ”. This, along with an obvious need, provided the inspiration for this project.</p>

			<p>– Peter Gabriel</p>
